	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001123_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>50 Abermarle St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">29<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> Oct<hi rend="sup">r</hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>Having been 
<lb/>advised by my 
<lb/>friends to delay my 
<lb/>visit to <placeName>Portugal</placeName>
<lb/>for a week or so 
<lb/>on account of 
<lb/>the epidemic now 
<lb/>raging at <placeName>Lisbon</placeName>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001123_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>I have <add place="above">thought</add> that I might 
<lb/>accomplish my 
<lb/>visit to <placeName>Bradford</placeName>
<lb/>in the meantime, 
<lb/>and therefore propose 
<lb/>to go thither on <choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>uesday 
<lb/>the 10<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> Nov<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> if 
<lb/>that day will be 
<lb/>convenient for the 
<lb/>friends there. </p>
<lb/><p>The Mayor kindly 
<lb/>invited me to his 
<lb/>house and I believe 
<lb/>that I have a 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001123_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>similar invitation 
<lb/>from yourself. I feel 
<lb/>much obliged to you 
<lb/>both and as I am 
<lb/>quite content with 
<lb/>the smallest accom
<lb/>modation I should 
<lb/>like to accept 
<lb/>of that which will 
<lb/>entail the least 
<lb/>trouble. I am not 
<lb/>aware whether <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Darlington</persName> with 
<lb/>whom I have 
<w>cor-<lb break="no"/>responded</w> is the Mayor 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001123_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/>but if either you 
<lb/>or he will drop 
<lb/>a line of directions 
<lb/>you will much 
<lb/>oblige yours &amp;c 
<lb/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p><persName>Titus Salt Esq.</persName></p>
			
